
Window Attribute Tags (V39)
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_NewLookMenus: ( ti_Tag=$80000093 )

Specify a boolean in ti_Data for whether
or not NewLook menus are required.


Window Attribute Tags (V39)
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_AmigaKey: ( ti_Tag=$80000094 )

Specify a pointer to an Image structure 
in ti_Data to use a custom Amiga-key
image for the menus.


Window Attribute Tags (V39)
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_NotifyDepth: ( ti_Tag=$80000095 )

Specify a boolean True to request 
IDCMP_CHANGEWINDOW messages when window 
is depth arranged. (imsg->Code = CWCODE_DEPTH)


Window Attribute Tags (V39)
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_Pointer: ( ti_Tag=$80000097 )

Specify a new Mouse Pointer to use in the
window. ti_Data contains a pointer to a
pointer object obtained via "pointerclass".


Window Attribute Tags (V39)
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_BusyPointer: ( ti_Tag=$80000098 )

Specify a True boolean to request the
standard busy pointer.


Window Attribute Tags (V39)
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_PointerDelay: ( ti_Tag=$80000099 )

Specify a True boolean to request that the
changing of the pointer be slightly delayed.
(To avoid the possibility of a flashing
pointer for short busy periods).


Window Attribute Tags (V39)
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_TabletMessages: ( ti_Tag=$8000009A )

Specify a True Boolean in ti_Data to request
that tablet information be included in
IntuiMessages sent to the window.
NB. Requires something to feed
IESUBCLASS_NEWTABLET InputEvents
into the system.


Window Attribute Tags (V39)
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_HelpGroup: ( ti_Tag=$8000009B )

When the active window has gadget help enabled,
other windows of the same HelpGroup number
will also get GadgetHelp.  This allows GadgetHelp
to work for multi-windowed applications.
Use GetGroupID() to get an ID number.  Pass
this number as ti_Data to all your windows.


Window Attribute Tags (V39)
=====================

Usage: OpenWindowTagList_/Windowtags

WA_HelpGroupWindow: ( ti_Tag=$8000009B )

When the active window has gadget help enabled,
other windows of the same HelpGroup will also get
GadgetHelp. This allows GadgetHelp to work
for multi-windowed applications.  As an alternative
to WA_HelpGroup, you can pass a pointer to any
other window of the same group to join its help
group.  Defaults to NULL, which has no effect.

